<h2 id="miscellaneous">Miscellaneous</h2>
<h3>What's your Vim configuration?</h3>
<p>I'm a returning VIM afficonado, after many years away, so am making good use of <a href="http://vim.spf13.com" title="The Ultimate VIM Distribution">SPF13</a> to take care of a lot of the configuration for me. If you want to know more, then check out the site. It has a lot on offer, including Vundle, NerdTree, Surround, PIV, Tabularize and more.</p>
<h3>What tools do you use? What's your video workflow?</h3>
<p>I don't use a particularly complicated or sophisticated setup. I'm planning to write a blog post about it in the semi-near future. In short, I use Screenflow 4, GarageBand (though I'm thinking of checking out Audacity), VIM, and Chromium. It's not that sophisticated, in that I follow a simple approach of scripting each episode, recording the code, recording the audio and tidying everything up. I'll say more in an upcoming post.</p>
